# Key Learnings

- Pandas is built on top of NumPy and provides efficient tools for handling structured datasets.
- Series represents one-dimensional labeled data.
- DataFrames represent two-dimensional tabular data.
- `.loc[]` performs label-based indexing, whereas `.iloc[]` performs position-based indexing.
- Boolean filtering allows efficient data selection.
- GroupBy operations simplify data aggregation.
- Pivot Tables and Crosstabs summarize large datasets efficiently.
- Merge and Concat help combine multiple datasets.
- Apply and Map simplify custom transformations.

